.TH AXIOM 1 "2025" "Axiom" "User Commands"
.
.SH NAME
axiom \- a minimal terminal text editor
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B axiom
[\fIfile\fR]
.br
.B axiom
.B \-\-version
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B axiom
is a terminal text editor written in C with no external dependencies.
It uses raw terminal I/O and VT100 escape sequences for rendering.
It supports syntax highlighting, multiple buffers, visual selection,
incremental search, mouse scroll, line numbers, and a configuration
file for customising behaviour.
.PP
If \fIfile\fR is given, it is opened for editing. If no file is given,
axiom starts with an empty unnamed buffer.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version number and exit.
.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.SS File Operations
.TP
.B Ctrl\-S
Save the current buffer. Prompts for a filename if the buffer is unnamed.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-Q
Quit. If there are unsaved changes in any buffer, requires confirmation
by pressing Ctrl\-Q multiple times (configurable via \fIquit_times\fR).
.TP
.B Ctrl\-F
Incremental search. Use arrow keys to move between matches.
Press \fBEscape\fR to cancel.
.SS Editing
.TP
.B Tab
Insert spaces up to the next tab stop (configurable via \fItab_stop\fR).
.TP
.B Backspace
Delete the character before the cursor. If the cursor is preceded by a
full tab stop worth of spaces, deletes them all at once.
.TP
.B Enter
Insert a new line, auto-indented to match the current line.
.SS Selection and Clipboard
.TP
.B Ctrl\-K
Toggle visual line selection mode. Move the cursor to extend the selection.
Press \fBCtrl\-K\fR or \fBEscape\fR to cancel.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-C
Copy the current selection. If no selection is active, copies the current line.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-V
Paste the clipboard contents at the cursor position.
.SS Buffer Management
.TP
.B Ctrl\-T
Open a new empty buffer.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-W
Close the current buffer. Blocked if the buffer has unsaved changes.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-Right
Switch to the next buffer.
.TP
.B Ctrl\-Left
Switch to the previous buffer.
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B Arrow keys
Move the cursor one character or line at a time.
.TP
.B Page Up / Page Down
Scroll one screen at a time.
.TP
.B Home / End
Move to the start or end of the current line.
.TP
.B Mouse scroll
Scroll up or down (speed configurable via \fIscroll_speed\fR).
.
.SH CONFIGURATION
axiom reads
.I ~/.axiomrc
on startup. Lines beginning with
.B #
are treated as comments. Each option is written as:
.PP
.RS
.I key
=
.I value
.RE
.PP
The following options are supported:
.TP
.B tab_stop
Number of spaces per tab stop. Default:
.BR 8 .
.TP
.B quit_times
Number of Ctrl\-Q presses required to quit with unsaved changes. Default:
.BR 3 .
.TP
.B scroll_speed
Number of lines scrolled per mouse wheel tick. Default:
.BR 3 .
.TP
.B key_new_buffer
Key binding to open a new buffer. Default:
.BR ctrl\-t .
.TP
.B key_close_buffer
Key binding to close the current buffer. Default:
.BR ctrl\-w .
.TP
.B key_next_buffer
Key binding to switch to the next buffer. Default:
.BR ctrl\-right .
.TP
.B key_prev_buffer
Key binding to switch to the previous buffer. Default:
.BR ctrl\-left .
.PP
Accepted key formats:
.BR ctrl\-a " through " ctrl\-z ", " ctrl\-left ", " ctrl\-right .
.PP
See
.I .axiomrc.example
in the source repository for a fully annotated template.
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.axiomrc
User configuration file. Read on startup if it exists.
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/axiom
Default install location.
.TP
.I /usr/local/share/man/man1/axiom.1.gz
This man page.
.
.SH SYNTAX HIGHLIGHTING
axiom detects the file type from the file extension and applies
syntax highlighting automatically. Supported languages:
.PP
.RS
C and C++ (.c, .h, .cpp, .hpp, .cc),
Python (.py),
Go (.go),
Rust (.rs)
.RE
.
